process_definition_structure.json_schema:
{
  "processId": "string (kebab-case)",
  "processName": "string (human-readable)",
  "description": "string",
  "processType": "end-to-end|subprocess|decision|interaction",
  "context": "string (business context)",
  "actors": [
    {
      "id": "string",
      "name": "string",
      "type": "human|system"
    }
  ],
  "activities": [
    {
      "id": "string",
      "name": "string",
      "type": "userTask|serviceTask|manualTask|scriptTask",
      "actor": "string (actor id)",
      "description": "string",
      "inputData": ["business object names"],
      "outputData": ["business object names"]
    }
  ],
  "gateways": [
    {
      "id": "string",
      "name": "string",
      "type": "exclusive|parallel|inclusive",
      "conditions": [
        {
          "path": "string",
          "condition": "string (condition expression)"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "dataObjects": [
    {
      "id": "string",
      "name": "string",
      "path": "string (relative path to JSON file)"
    }
  ],
  "integrations": [
    {
      "name": "string",
      "type": "API|Service|Database",
      "activity": "string (activity id)",
      "description": "string"
    }
  ],
  "estimatedDuration": "string",
  "complexity": "low|medium|high",
  "generatedFrom": "string (source document path)",
  "generatedDate": "string (ISO 8601)"
}

pattern.template:
```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant {actor1}
    participant {actor2}
    participant {actor3}

    {actor1}->>{actor2}: {message1}
    {actor2}->>{actor2}: {internal_action}
    {actor2}->>{actor3}: {message2}
    {actor3}->>{actor1}: {response}

    Note over {actor1},{actor3}: {important_note}
```

example.code:
from toolkit_packager.generators.process_generator import generate_process_markdown
process_def = { "processId": "new-business-application", "processName": "New Business Application Process", "description": "End-to-end process for new policy applications", "processType": "end-to-end", "context": "LifeInsuranceAndAnnuities", "actors": [ {"id": "agent", "name": "Insurance Agent", "type": "human"}, {"id": "system", "name": "BAW System", "type": "system"} ], "activities": [ { "id": "collect_app", "name": "Collect Application Data", "type": "userTask", "actor": "agent", "inputData": [], "outputData": ["Application", "Policyholder"] } ] }
output_path = Path("business-processes/LifeInsuranceAndAnnuities") generate_process_markdown(process_def, "LifeInsuranceAndAnnuities", output_path)
